an rogue and human ranger.<br>
<br>
We both would like to roleplay good vs evil. We would PK evil races when possible (and the occasional evil gnome necro), but would only PK light races out of self defense or if they have an &quot;evil&quot; reputation.<br>
<br>
I was wondering what &quot;lightie&quot; guilds would fit this definition and have good reputations. While we want to attack darkies, we have no intention of being &quot;grief&quot; players and would want to make sure we are in an honorable guild (ie, no cropse camping, no portal camping, no zone camping, etc).<br>
<br>
We're planning on leveling up to about 20th on our own over the next few weeks, to prove ourselves and get a feel for the server. But, I'd like to know if there are any good guilds that we should try and meet up with that match our goals. Any info you can provide would be appreciated.<br>
<br>
Tarak Kamatayan<br>
Tholuxe Paells<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utarakkamatayan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tarak Kamatayan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/26/01 3:17:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tallon Zek political structure?</span><hr size=1> Blech! I just read the PvP discussion threads on whineplay. Nevermind. I don't think I could stand playing on a Zek server for very long.<br>
<br>
Call me naive, but I hadn't imagined problems like delevelers, cross-team healers, and out-of-range healers. The whole thing sounds ugly to me.<br>
<br>
Maybe they will make a good vs evil PvP server and take care of some of these issues that are causing problems in the current servers. Then I'll give it a try.<br>
<br>
Adios<br>
TK from TP <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/26/01 7:29:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tallon Zek political structure?</span><hr size=1> don't let that keep you from playing.. it's not like that sort of thing happens every second of every day in every zone.. i'm sure it's pretty rare and limited to the newbie zones if it's anything like rallos zek. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udinadaandedenaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dinadaan DeDenaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/17/01 6:34:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tallon Zek political structure?</span><hr size=1> Try The Highland Army. They been around forever and to many of them their guild is their heart and soul.<br>
<br>
Just stay away from Tallon Zek Times. ITS   EVIL  !!!<br>
<br>
Here is a link, lol:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub7.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735generaldiscussion">pub7.ezboard.com/ftallonz...discussion</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uitzena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Itzena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/01 4:40:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tallon Zek political structure?</span><hr size=1> Um, you want to play GvE but are worried about xteaming?<br>
<br>
Anyone else see the contradiction here? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uelenwyyi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elenwyyi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/24/01 8:08:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bah.</span><hr size=1> I went to TZ thinking with the GvE mentality too; lets just say that's not the way I look at things now. And I would take what I read on the message boards with a grain of salt (although I'd still read them, helps to know who the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.thewebforge.com/tallonzektimes/">neighbors</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> are.<br>
<br>
PvP can be a lot of fun, don't go there with a bunch of preconceived ideas about what to expect (things change, and you're usually wrong to begin with).<br>
<br>
Lots of people play GvE<br>
Lots of people play Every team for itself<br>
A few (strong minority) people play 4-teams.<br>
<br>
You could go there with your friend and play GvE, but you'd be in for a few surprises from your &quot;good&quot; team members.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utarakkamatayan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tarak Kamatayan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/01 11:14:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bah.</span><hr size=1> Well, I've spent the last month on TZ. My friend and I discovered that it was pretty impossible to play GvsE the way we wanted to play it. However, it's pretty easy to play EvsG.<br>
<br>
In other words, it was frustrating to play a good player who only fought against evil because many of the &quot;good&quot; characters are not good. It didn't feel right when an elven paladin of Tunare (you would think this would be a &quot;good&quot; character from the roleplaying perspective) attacked and killed a human ranger. I realize that the team PvP server is supposed to allow this, but it didn't fit my roleplaying needs.<br>
<br>
However, my friend and I made dark team characters and are roleplaying evil. That's much easier. I don't have a problem with a dark elf killing a human necromancer. It is still consistent with my &quot;evil vs good&quot; roleplaying mentality. Anyway, I've warmed to the server, and have encountered less crossteaming, out of range healing, corpse camping, bind rushing, etc than I feared. I'm hooked.<br>
<br>
I'm not even that into player killing. The thing I like about the server is that there is a simple way to resolve many disputes: might makes right. If some non-dark team people are camping something I want to camp, I drive them off or leave them alone (depending on how tough they are). There's no question of sharing, or taking turns, or who was there first. Refreshing. There's still lots of whining, but the bottom line is that you're either tough enough to do what you want, or you're not. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/01 4:57:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bah.</span><hr size=1> You should check out the "Roleplaying Server" thread on whineplay.  Throw your input in there. <p>Majestyk, <a href="http://Server3.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse">Rogue</a>, <a href="http://www.talonguard.org/shanks">Shanks</a>, <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5034">Vallon Zek!</a>

We as Shanks, have chosen the hard path. In the hardness of it, is where we find the glory.</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessage?topicID=165.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessage?topicID=164.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.emailToFriend?topicID=130.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.threadControl?topicID=130.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=130.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=130.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<option value="thesafehousetherootcellar">The Root Cellar<option value="thesafehouselaboratory">Laboratory<option value="th